Description.div: On the following pages you will be asked %System_NumberOfQuestions% questions about Knowing Your Customer - AML/CTF Programs

You may be asked 3 different types of questions: multiple choice, true/false or yes/no. Answer each question by clicking the button to the left of the most appropriate response.
After you answer the last question, you will be given the chance to review and then submit your answers.
Please note that if you Exit the quiz before clicking the Submit Answers button then your answers will not be saved.
To move between questions, use the Previous and Next navigation buttons on the bottom right of the page.

Description.strong: Money laundering and terrorism financing risk is the risk that a reporting entity may reasonably face that the provision of its designated services might involve or facilitate money laundering or the financing of terrorism. True or false?
Choose the best answer. In determining its money laundering/terrorist financing risk, your organisation must consider:

Answer.Description: The types of customers it has and the types of designated services it provides
The methods of delivery its designated services
The foreign jurisdictions with which it deals

Description.strong: It is your obligation to comply with the requirements and procedures of your organisation's AML/CTF Program to the extent that it is relevant to your role and duties. True or false?
From what date must every reporting entity have and comply with an AML/CTF Program?
Your organisation can commence to provide a designated service to a customer after 12 December 2007 even if it has not adopted and does not maintain an AML/CTF Program. True or false?

A Standard AML/CTF Program contains two parts – Part A (setting out systems and controls designed to identify, mitigate ML/TF risk) and Part B (applicable customer identification procedures). True or false?
This online training course forms part of your organisation's AML/CTF awareness training. True or false?
Choose the best answer. Part A of your organisation's AML/CTF Program sets out:

Answer.Description: Procedures to enable your organisation to identify significant changes in money laundering/terrorist financing risk
Systems and controls designed to identify, mitigate and manage your organisation's money laundering/terrorist financing risk

Description.strong: Choose the best answer. Part B of your organisation's AML/CTF Program must address:

Answer.Description: The procedures to be followed to identify customers
The procedures to be followed in making reports to the AUSTRAC CEO
The procedures to be followed in verifying the identity of customers
The procedures to be followed to identify and verify the identity of customers
